<br>
1)- Fuel decay life-time, which in the case of Pu238 is 86.8 yrs. So this means that in 50 yrs it would be greatly reduced.<br>
<br>
2)- Thermocouple junction operational life time, as I mentioned before. When this one is deteriorated (surface material deterioration..) then the temperature difference across the junction drastically decreases and this in turn is directly related to its thermal-electric conversion efficiency. <p>&quot;The greatest people have always experienced the greatest opposition. I am honored&quot;. Ihrenes</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2566<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/24/02 7:46:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/3.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RTG Rovers</span><hr size=1> What is the range of Thermocouple junction operational life times then? Is this a serious obstacle to developing an RTG Rover? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=184.topic&start=21&stop=21>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=184.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=184.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http